# Storybook Patterns

## Key Rules
1. Every component needs a story
2. Export config directly (no intermediate `meta` variable)
3. Mirror component hierarchy in story titles
4. Use MDX for complex component docs

## Story Structure
```typescript
import type { Meta, StoryObj } from '@storybook/react'
import { Button } from './button'

export default {
  title: 'Components/Button',
  component: Button,
} satisfies Meta<typeof Button>

type Story = StoryObj<typeof Button>

export const Default: Story = {}

export const Primary: Story = {
  args: { variant: 'primary' }
}
```

